The evaluation of the audit is based on the evaluation criteria provided in the Babtec questionnaire.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;For process audits according to VDA 6.3, the specifications for evaluation from the VDA volume must be observed.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;If possible, objective evidence of the deviations should be collected and filed in BabtecAUDIT. For this purpose, documents can be scanned or photos taken in the audit.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;The following applies to the classification of deviations:

&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;<b>MajorNC</b>&#13;&#10;
Whole sections of the standard or the own QM-documentation, which are the basis of the audit, were not processed or during an activity in the company requirements of the standard / the QM-documentation are systematically not used.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;

<b>MinorNC</b>&#13;&#10;
A single nonconformity from the requirements. A number of minor nonconformities from a specific requirement can be classified as a major deviation.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;

<b>Potential/Recommendation</b>&#13;&#10;
Improvement suggestion discovered by the auditor in the process.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;<b>Send report </b>&#13;&#10;The report including deviations must be sent to the audited process owner promptly after the audit. The Director QMS must be set to CC.
